title: Mayday Air Crash Investigations S01 E04 Flying on Empty DVD 720p
description:
Flying on Empty

Aired on 10/08/2003, Narrated by Stephen Bogaert

On 24 August 2001, Air Transat Flight 236, an Airbus A330-200, runs out of fuel while flying over the Atlantic Ocean. The pilots of the aircraft glide it to a safe landing on a runway at a naval base on an island in the Azores. The fuel starvation was caused by improper maintenance work which allowed a hydraulic oil pipe and a fuel pipe to rub together, resulting in the fracture of the fuel pipe and consequent leak.
